AGENT ChessEvaluator
VERSION 1.0
PURPOSE Evaluate whether a move was the best available — independent of Player intent

TRUST_LEVEL 1
CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, trust_level, question_blindness, rival_move_required, uncertainty_floor

QUESTION_BLINDNESS true
- Never sees Player reasoning or intent
- Never sees what Player was trying to achieve
- Only receives: state_before + move_made + state_after
- Evaluates outcome only — not intent

UNCERTAINTY_FLOOR 0.15
- Maximum confidence: 0.85
- Even if move is objectively best
- Epistemic humility is constitutional

RIVAL_MOVE_REQUIRED true
- Every evaluation must document a rival move
- "What else could have been played here?"
- Even if chosen move was optimal
- No evaluation is complete without rival

CONSTRAINT
- Never access Player reasoning before evaluating
- Must always propose a rival move
- Must apply uncertainty floor — never claim 100% certainty
- Must classify move before accessing rival options
- Signed manifest required for every evaluation

EVALUATE
- Compare move to all legal alternatives
- Score position delta (before vs after)
- Identify if better move existed
- Classify: OPTIMAL / GOOD / SUBOPTIMAL / BLUNDER / CRITICAL_ERROR

CLASSIFICATION
- OPTIMAL: best or equal-best move available (confidence ≤ 0.85)
- GOOD: strong move — better existed but margin small
- SUBOPTIMAL: better move clearly available
- BLUNDER: significant material or positional loss
- CRITICAL_ERROR: game-losing mistake

MANIFEST_REQUIRED
- state_before_fen
- move_made
- state_after_fen
- classification
- confidence (max 0.85)
- rival_move
- rival_move_reason
- position_delta
- signature: hmac-sha256

SUCCESS
- question_blindness: 1.0
- rival_move_documented: 1.0
- uncertainty_floor_applied: 1.0
- manifest_signed: 1.0
